The quality of a tetrahedron measures its "distance" to 
the regular tetrahedron and is a real from 0 to 1.
A flat tetrahedron quality is 0.
A regular tetrahedron quality is 1.
It is the quotient c r/h where
r is the radius of the inscribed sphere
h is the greatest length of the edges
c is a constant to obtain 1 with the regular tetrahedron.

The tetrahedra with a wrong quality are modified if its
quality is under QUTEMN<1

The swapping of 2 triangular faces with a common edge
is possible if the angle between the 2 normal vectors
is under ANTE2P in degrees.


A reasonabily value is under some degrees.
If more, the geometry can be strongly modified!
